    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A predominantly pale green marble with white markings that is quarried near Clifden in County Galway, Ireland. A metamorphosed dolomitic limestone, it is considered to be one of two true marbles native to the British Isles, the other being Iona marble.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
